  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I guess we should choose to add `color: $black` instead of removing the background color. In case of websites, that only implemented their own text color but not a background color, removing `background: $white` might result in similar problems as described by @Majkl578.\r\n\r\nIf we keep `background: $white`, the compatibility is still given for those who didn't configured their own background color. Adding `color: $black` will keep the search-box text readable for every desktop theme.\r\nFor the integration on a website, the colors should be set anyway by the designer to prevent off-colored results.",
    "created_at": "2018-08-25T17:39:10Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3075#issuecomment-415985165",
    "id": 415985165,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3075",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxNTk4NTE2NQ==",
